My perfect nachos would be a perfect ratio of hot and cold ingredients, and a perfect ratio of tortilla chip to ingredients.  All tortilla chips should remain crunchy.  Layer tortilla chips on a large plate.  Scoop a small dollop of cooked refried or back beans on each chip.  Generously spread shredded 4 cheese Mexican cheese over all tortilla chips - make sure to fully cover each chip.  Microwave to fully melt cheese.   Then, top with pico de gallo, guac, sour cream and cilantro.
